Looks good to me. I might have chosen a different name for "DONE_WITH_CLOSE". To my ears, this suggests that we are done closing, but from the code I see that it means, "done, except we still need to do a close". "DONE_EXCEPT_CLOSE" might have been a little better. But I don't think this should hold back the commit.

The code looks good to me, but like others commented in the JIRA, I'm not quite convinced that this really helps a lot. Dave pointed out that it does not allow transactional operations on native HBase tables. Also, we still need to load Trafodion code into the region server, so in that sense we are still intrusive, and probably always will be.

This code allows us to use specific coprocessors for individual tables. That may be a good thing, but it could also be problematic, e.g. if we want to change all the coprocessors.

About the need for restarting HBase: If we add a new jar, that would have to be in the classpath of the region server. Wouldn't that require a restart of HBase, regardless of whether we change the hbase_coprocessor_region_classes configuration entry or not?

I don't think it can actually build the documents since I forgot to add the
new docs/shared folder. Checking.
